###
# Bookora API - HTTP Test Files
# ==============================
#
# This directory contains HTTP files for manual testing of the Bookora API.
# Run these tests using IntelliJ IDEA's HTTP Client.
#
# File Structure:
# ---------------
# - README.http                    : This file, usage guide
# - http-client.env.json          : Environment configurations (dev/staging/prod)
# - auth.http                     : Authentication tests (register, login, refresh, logout)
# - email-verification.http       : Email verification tests
# - guest-booking.http            : Guest booking tests
#
# How to Use:
# -----------
# 1. Open any .http file in IntelliJ IDEA
# 2. Select environment at the top (dev/staging/prod)
# 3. Click ▶️ icon next to the request or press Ctrl+Enter
# 4. View response (includes automatic validation scripts)
#
# Recommended Test Order:
# -----------------------
# 1. auth.http           → Register, login to obtain tokens
# 2. email-verification.http → Email verification flow
# 3. guest-booking.http  → Guest booking workflow
#
# Important Notes:
# ----------------
# - Some tests use response values (tokens, etc.) from previous tests
# - Running tests in sequence will automatically set variables
# - Read comments in each section to prepare necessary data
# - Some tests expect specific database state
#
# Environment Configuration:
# --------------------------
# Configure environment-specific baseUrl in http-client.env.json
# Current settings:
# - dev     : http://localhost:8080/api
# - staging : https://staging.bookora.com/api
# - prod    : https://api.bookora.com/api
#
